summary: Want a healthier heart? Eat a steak [Opinion]
title: Want a healthier heart? Eat a steak [Opinion]
excerpt: I'm a cardiologist — and I encourage patients to eat red meat. This advice defies conventional wisdom. For decades, nutritionists and physicians have urged people to limit consumption of red meat and other fatty foods, which were thought to cause heart disease. But new studies debunk this conventional wisdom. Indeed, it now looks like low-quality carbohydrates — not saturated fats — are driving America's heart disease epidemic. It's time to stop demonizing steak. The medical community frowns upon the kinds of saturated fats found in meat, dairy and coconut oil.

summary: Basics Relating to Free Radicals and Antioxidants
title: Basics Relating to Free Radicals and Antioxidants
body:
Antioxidant vitamins offer the influence to bring these free radicals under control. They accomplish this by just meeting the free radicals’ most elementary needs, by granting them the electrons they need to be stable. In result, we end up with health and well being that is freed from free radicals that are out to obliterate our cells as well as our all round healthy wellness.


Free radicals essentially perform a significant role in numerous biological operations, many of which are necessary for life, including intracellular killing of bacteria by neutrophil granulocytes. They have also been suggested as a factor in certain cell signaling processes. The two most significant oxygen-centered free radicals are superoxide and hydroxyl radical. They are simply derived from molecular oxygen in reducing conditions, such as every time a person breathes.


Because of the high reactivity, free radicals typically participate in unwanted side reactions contributing to cell impairment. Multiple kinds of cancer can be the result of chemical reactions between free radicals and DNA, which results in mutations that can negatively affect the cell cycle and then potentially result in malignancy. Scientists also have indicated free radicals as the reason behind some of the signs of aging, including atherosclerosis, alcohol-induced liver damage, alpha 1-antitrypsin in the lung, and even chronic lung disorders.



The main antioxidant vitamins are Vitamin E, Vitamin C and Vitamin A. All these antioxidant nutritional vitamins actually have the power to act as “stand alone” catalysts for a more healthy you. So, free radicals prove to be no match to them. Moreover, these antioxidant vitamins can in fact help us to get rid of these free radicals which may ultimately deny us of our healthy and balanced well-being..


Check out a valuable antioxidant you can have in drinking water!


So what on earth might be richer in antioxidants when compared to the beloved wild blueberry? Well, think about the small red bean? You got it!  I suggested “bean.” The small red bean actually provides more antioxidants per serving size than the wild blueberry. And the red kidney bean as well as pinto bean convey more antioxidants per serving size than the usual serving of cultivated blueberries.
